Feb 2 2008 	Great for the budget traveler!	I stayed at the Harmony in May 07. I was planning my own trip to China without a agency to try and save money. I expected a $35 a night hotel to be almost like camping but I thought I could live with that since I wouldn't be spending much time in the room. The location is across the street from the main train station but it far enough down a side street that it is quiet. Even though some reviews say that they did not like this, I felt safer than in most American cities except from &quot;human spam&quot; (people trying to sell you stuff, which is everywhere in China). The rooms are similar to what you would find in a &quot;Holiday Inn&quot; or similar chain. There is only a shower and not a tub, but that did not bother me at all. The beds were clean but, like every hotel in China, harder than American standard. The front desk employees spoke English very well and were helpful but not a concierge. One good thing was that they were not trying to sell you things, like I have seen in other Asian countries. The breakfasts were expensive by Chinese standards but not for American standards and I thought they were quite good. The in-room massages are inexpensive and wonderful after a day climbing the great wall. They did not seem at all to be like massages in Thailand which is just another word for &quot;special services&quot;. In all, I think this is a very affordable hotel and exceeded my expectations. If I ever go back to Beijing, I will be booking this hotel again.	
