Jan 16 2007 	Good budget hotel. Great location for Beijing train station	Stayed at the hotel for two nights in January at the end of my trip on the Trans-Mongolian railway. I wanted somewhere near the main train station and you can't get any nearer without being inside the station.This is a mid range to budget hotel, so expect that level of service and standards and you will be happy with your stay. If you want more, pay more (room cost 25 pounds a night!) and stay somewhere else. The staff spoke functional English and were as helpful as they were asked to be. The front doorman seems to go walkabout in the evening, so if security is a main concern this could be an issue. While you get a room card, people are free to come and go throughout the hotel and being this close to the station there's likely more traffic than they can keep track of. Didn't try either the bar or restaurant, but the restaurant seems to close quite early.The room was of standard size and clean. The bathroom counter and sink were nice, but the shower cubicle was more in line with hostel standards and the exposed pipes gave it a bad DIY feel.The location really is good. There's a shop right across the street which served as an unofficial room service for getting drinks and snacks. There are a number of cheap food alternatives there as well. The Beijingzhan metro stop is around the corner and the Chongwenmen metro station is 5 minutes walk. You can walk to Tiananmen square in 25 minutes by taking a right down Beijing Zhan Xijie and following it onto Qianmen Dongdajie. Conversely you can take the Metro from Beijingzhan to Quianmen (the previous reviewer saying you have to change trains and go to Tiananmen XI is just adding stops that don't need to be made). Unless its raining I'd also say its not too much to ask to walk to and from the Wangfujing shopping area.To find the hotel from Beijing Station:Come out the main entrance of the station and look across the street to your left and find the building with the China Post sign on it. There is also a McDonald's visible and lots of other shops and colourful signs. Simply cross the street and walk around the left hand corner (as seen with your back to the train station) of that building and you will see the Harmony Hotel if you don't spot the sign for it first. If it helps, one of my pics is looking back towards the station from the hotel.Airport Shuttle Bus from Beijing Station:If you want to take the shuttle bus to the airport (runs every 15 mins, approx 1 hour and 16Y) then from the hotel cross the road as if going back into Beijing railway station, but while facing the KFC take a right down the slip road. After 100 metres you should see the shuttle buses or at least the stand where they leave from. A cheap and simple alternative to taking a taxi. From the pic I have looking at the station you can see a bus parked there. Go 100 metres right of where that bus is to find the airport shuttle.	
