Oct 29 2006 	Good location clean room good access to food	Room was very clean. Carpet and furniture appeared to be no more than 1 year old. The bathroom was clean but looked dated. Hotel staff were helpful - they helped us with the safe and shower knob issues within 10 mins and refused to accept tips. The lady at the reception was having a bad day when we checked it. She slammed down the phone after speaking with a colleague but was polite to us. LOCATIONHotel is a 2 min walk to the Beijing railway station and subway (Beijingzhan station). Hotel is location north of the station. A taxi ride to Chaoyang District (for shopping) costs 20 to 30 yuan. If you are going to Tiananmen Square, take a train to Tiananmen east station (you need to change train at jianguomen station). Subway tickets cost 3 yuan per ride per person. FOODThere are a number of good local and fast food eateries within a 2 min walk. As you walk from the hotel to the station (10m from hotel), you will see a shop with steaming buns and dumplings just next door to the hotel (not the one closest to the hotel) - delicious jiao zhi (dumplings) and buns (xiao long bao) for 3 yuan a basket (containing 10 each basket). Yummy!For good local dinner, follow the slip road in the right when you exit the hotel. There a shop with a picture of a mosque hung in the restaurant. It is a Chinese Muslim eatery. We had a large bowl of beef noodles (Nui Rou La Mian), 20 pieces of beef dumplings (jiao zhi), spicy beancurd skin fried with green peppers and a bottle of beer all for 20 yuan. Yummy!There are supermarkets and minimarts in the building opposite the hotel.	
